The paper deals with two-player zero-sum games, which are typically studied in the area of game theory (cs.GT). The use of reachability objectives and finite arenas suggests a connection to the area of formal verification and automata theory (cs.DS, cs.LO). The mention of randomized actions and probability suggests a connection to the area of probabilistic algorithms and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of reduction from Countdown Games suggests a connection to the area of complexity theory and computational complexity (cs.CC).
